---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'AI Insurance Workflow Automation — Jonathan Abraham';
const description = 'A practical workflow turning messy quote emails, PDFs, and intake notes into structured tasks, missing-information checks, and CRM-ready data.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description} showBoot={false}>
  <main id="content" class="doc">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="crumbs">
        <a href="/">~</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="/#proof-of-work">proof-of-work</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>insurance-workflow</span>
      </div>
      <div class="prompt">&gt; ./projects/insurance-workflow</div>
      <h1 class="h doc">AI Insurance Workflow Automation</h1>
      <p class="sub">A practical workflow turning messy quote emails, PDFs, and intake notes into structured tasks, missing-info checks, and CRM-ready data.</p>
      <div class="meta-row">
        <span><b>status</b> v1.2 · production</span>
        <span><b>year</b> 2025</span>
        <span><b>role</b> ai systems engineer</span>
        <span><b>stack</b> python · langgraph · postgres · s3</span>
      </div>
      <div style="margin:0 0 28px">
        <span class="tag">AI</span><span class="tag">Documents</span><span class="tag">CRM</span><span class="tag">Workflow</span><span class="tag">Human-in-loop</span>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-grid">
        <article class="prose">
          <div class="schem">
            <div class="schem-head"><span>// workflow.dag</span><span>v1.2</span></div>
            <svg viewBox="0 0 720 280" aria-hidden="true">
              <defs><marker id="ai2" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="7" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 z" fill="#6ee7ff"/></marker></defs>
              <g stroke="#6ee7ff" stroke-width="1.4" fill="none" marker-end="url(#ai2)">
                <path d="M90 140 L210 70"/><path d="M90 140 L210 140"/><path d="M90 140 L210 210"/>
                <path d="M310 70 L430 140"/><path d="M310 140 L430 140"/><path d="M310 210 L430 140"/>
                <path d="M530 140 L630 70"/><path d="M530 140 L630 140"/><path d="M530 140 L630 210"/>
              </g>
              <g fill="#0a0e0b" stroke="#6ee7ff" stroke-width="1.4">
                <rect x="20" y="120" width="80" height="40"/>
                <rect x="210" y="50" width="100" height="40"/>
                <rect x="210" y="120" width="100" height="40"/>
                <rect x="210" y="190" width="100" height="40"/>
                <rect x="430" y="120" width="100" height="40"/>
                <rect x="630" y="50" width="80" height="40"/>
                <rect x="630" y="120" width="80" height="40"/>
                <rect x="630" y="190" width="80" height="40"/>
              </g>
              <g fill="#cfe9d3" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="11">
                <text x="38" y="144">INBOX</text>
                <text x="232" y="74">EMAIL</text>
                <text x="240" y="144">PDF</text>
                <text x="232" y="214">NOTE</text>
                <text x="446" y="144">EXTRACT</text>
                <text x="652" y="74">CRM</text>
                <text x="640" y="144">REVIEW</text>
                <text x="650" y="214">FLAG</text>
              </g>
            </svg>
          </div>

          <p><strong>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet</strong>, consectetur adipiscing elit. Insurance brokers receive quote requests as a chaotic mix of forwarded emails, PDF attachments, scanned forms, and free-text notes. The job of turning that mess into a clean record is high-volume, low-margin, and historically resistant to automation.</p>

          <p>This is a representative breakdown of a workflow I designed for a broker-side intake team. <em>Specifics anonymised</em>; the architecture is the lesson.</p>

          <h2>The problem</h2>
          <p>Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Each new quote required ~12 minutes of manual data entry across three systems, with a 7% rate of missing fields that triggered a back-and-forth email cycle averaging 36 hours.</p>

          <h2>Architecture</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Inbox watcher</strong> — IMAP + S3 staging; every artifact gets a content hash and a permanent URI.</li>
            <li><strong>Type router</strong> — small classifier decides email-body / PDF / scan / note; routes to the right extractor.</li>
            <li><strong>Extraction</strong> — schema-bound LLM calls per type, with confidence per field.</li>
            <li><strong>Missing-info checker</strong> — deterministic pass over the schema; auto-drafts a clarification email for review.</li>
            <li><strong>Human review</strong> — broker UI shows the source artifact next to the extracted record; approve / edit / reject.</li>
            <li><strong>CRM handoff</strong> — idempotent writer with retries; every field has provenance.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="callout">
            <b>// design note</b><br />
            Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident. The win wasn't a smarter LLM — it was making <strong>every extracted field traceable to a source span</strong>. That's what made brokers trust the output enough to skip re-reading.
          </div>

          <h2>Spec sheet</h2>
          <table class="spec">
            <tr><td class="k">throughput</td><td class="v">~ 240 quotes/day · single tenant</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">avg time saved</td><td class="v">9.5 min per quote</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">missing-info loop</td><td class="v">36h → 4h median</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">field provenance</td><td class="v">100% — source span linked</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">runtime</td><td class="v">python 3.12 · langgraph · postgres</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="k">deploy</td><td class="v">railway · single-region</td></tr>
          </table>

          <hr />
          <p><strong>Building something similar?</strong> <a href="/#contact">Get in touch</a>.</p>

          <div class="pn">
            <a class="pcard" href="/projects/voice-ai-intake"><small>← prev project</small><span>Voice AI Intake System</span></a>
            <a class="pcard next" href="/projects/web3-ops-agent"><small>next project →</small><span>Web3 Operations Agent</span></a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="toc" aria-label="contents">
          <h4>// contents</h4>
          <a href="#content">overview</a>
          <a href="#content">the problem</a>
          <a href="#content">architecture</a>
          <a href="#content">spec sheet</a>
        </aside>
      </div>
      <div class="ascii-div" aria-hidden="true">━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━</div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
